  <source>Istanbul University</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Evaluating predictive value of serum procalcitonin, C-Reactive Protein, drain IL-6 and
      TNF-alpha for anastomotic leakage in post-operative period.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      To search for a biomarker, which might be able to predict rectal anastomotic leakage before
      its clinical presentation. Serum procalcitonin, C-reactive protein, and drain fluid culture,
      IL-6 and TNF-α levels were evaluated in 50 consecutive patients with rectal cancer who
      underwent low anterior resection with colorectal anastomosis.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
